      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "I'd prefer the stateless method too, works better in case of concurrency. Ideally all the send\\* methods would go away, and be replaced with one send method that takes a structure that specifies the whole configuration (including addresses and amounts, fee/kb, maximum fee, confirm targets, minconfirms and such), instead of playing positional parameter bingo or changing defaults on the fly.\n",
